    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Rigshospitalet, Denmark</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of the study is to examine the relationship between working capacity (peak oxygen
      consumption) and pump speed of continuous flow left ventricular assist devices (CF-LVADs)in
      heart failure patients. The hypothesis is that it is possible to increase peak oxygen
      consumption by incrementally increasing CF-LVAD pumpspeed during exercise.

      The study population will consist of severe heart failure patients with CF-LVADs treated at
      The Heart Centre of Copenhagen University Hospital Rigshospitalet.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
